For PSI, we need finer granularity:

SNOOP_PAT:
- If set, look for input PAT, snoop it to get a list of input PMT PIDs

SNOOP_PMT:
- If set, look for input PMT, snoop it to get a list of input ES PIDs
- SNOOP_PAT should also be set

REMAP_PROG:
- if set, remap program number and PMT PIDs



For MPTS passthru:
  we snoop PAT/PMT just for show CLI.
  we regenerate PAT for TSID only.
  PMT PIDs remain unchanged in PAT.
  ES PIDs remain unchanged in PMT.

For MiniCarousel:
  we snoop PAT/PMT for show CLI.
  we regenerate PAT to include the MC program
  MC PMT PID remains unchanged in PAT.
  MC PMT sections remain unchanged.
  MC PIDs remain unchanged.
  

==========================================================================

- Should always drop input PAT.

- Should always rebuild output PAT with correct TSID.

- If psi_snooping is on, parse input PAT and PMT.
  Also merge all input PAT into output PAT,
  possible after PID/prog num remapping.

- If pid_remap is on, remap PMT PIDs and program numbers in input PAT,
  and ES PIDs in input PMTs.


Session modes:
- For SPTS muxing: pid_remap on, psi_snooping on.
- For MPTS passthru: pid_remap off, psi_snooping on.
- For data injection: pid_remap off, psi_snooping off.
- For MiniCarousel: pid_remap off, psi_snooping on.

